README sp-flash-tool-bin

    NOTES (FIXME: adjust to smdev)

    It may need to make your device visible for flash-tool by adding
    the device's IDs to udev rules.

    1. Connect the device to USB and check the information:

     $ lsusb
     Bus 001 Device 009: ID 04e8:6860 Samsung Electronics Co.,
     Ltd Galaxy series, misc. (MTP mode)

    2. Write /etc/udev/rules.d/99-ttyacms.rules using ID numbers:

     SUBSYSTEM=="usb", ATTR{idVendor}=="04e8", ATTR{idProduct}=="6860",
     MODE="0666", ENV{ID_MM_DEVICE_IGNORE}="1"

    3. Change file permissions and reload udev rules:

     # chmod a+r /etc/udev/rules.d/99-ttyacms.rules
     # udevadm control --reload-rules

    4. Replug the device and check if it works.

End of file.
